17/12/2002
ROME, Italy -- After a series of meetings in the Vatican on Monday (16 December), Croatian President Stipe Mesic said that Pope John Paul II would visit Croatia in the coming spring or summer. Tentatively, he plans to visit Dubrovnik, Rijeka, Zadar and possibly Osijek.
In other news, the leaders of the parties in Croatia's Parliament agreed to start consultations on a joint declaration in support of the EU accession process. The parties would support the government strategy for EU membership in a bid to speed up ongoing reforms crucial to meeting accession criteria. (Vjesnik, Vecernji List - 17/12/02; HINA, HRT - 16/12/02)
